cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "particle-pipeline: Automated SEM image analysis with physics-based DLS/RPS size estimation and GUM-compliant measurement uncertainty quantification"
authors:
  - family-names: "Ajayi"
    given-names: "Imoleayomide"
    affiliation: "Loughborough University"
version: 1.2.0
date-released: 2025-06-27
license: MIT
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20952534
repository-code: "https://github.com/imoleayomideajay/Particle-Pipeline-Package"
abstract: >-
  An open-source Python pipeline for automated scanning electron
  microscopy (SEM) particle size analysis. Implements adaptive
  threshold selection, watershed separation of touching particles,
  per-particle morphometry, Chan-Vese sub-pixel boundary refinement,
  physics-based cross-technique size estimation (Perrin-corrected DLS
  hydrodynamic diameter and prolate-spheroid RPS volume-equivalent
  diameter), and a seven-component GUM-compliant measurement
  uncertainty budget.
keywords:
  - scanning electron microscopy
  - particle size analysis
  - image segmentation
  - dynamic light scattering
  - resistive pulse sensing
  - measurement uncertainty
  - GUM
  - watershed segmentation
  - microplastics
  - nanoparticles
